        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>Sylvia Mendlow was a co-chairman of the United Federation of Teachers (UFT) Library Committee in New York City in the late 1960s. Her papers include correspondence, conference material, educational pamphlets, photographs, and newspaper clippings dating from the mid-1960s to the mid-1970s. The papers document the UFT's organization of librarians, as well as efforts to improve school library standards.</p>
